	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Cold morning conditions are expected across the country as the cold front passes on Wednesday.  Rain Scattered showers are expected between the Port Edward and Durban regions of KZN as the cold front passes. The rest of the country remains dry.  Temperatures Minimum temperatures are expected to be cold across the country as the cold front passes over the East Coast.Temperatures are expected to drop to near freezing in the Free State, and cooler weather is predicted for the central and northern parts of the country while the southern coastline, including the Eastern Cape, can expect moderate conditions. The coldest place in South Africa is expected to be Sutherland in the Northern Cape, dropping to a freezing 0°C. Maximum temperatures are expected to be moderate across the country, with cool temperatures across the Western Cape and the southern coastline as well as the southern parts of the Northern Cape.Temperatures are set to increase across the central and eastern parts of the country including the Free State, the North West, Gauteng and KZN, with warmer conditions along the northern border.The hottest places in South Africa will be Phalaborwa in Limpopo and Skukuza in Mpumalanga, reaching a high of 33°C. Click here to see the specific forecast for your city over the next few days Pretoria is expected to experience a maximum of 25°C, while Johannesburg is expected to have a high of 24°C. A high of 22°C is predicted for Bloemfontein. Along the coastal regions, Cape Town is expected to reach 19°C, Port Elizabeth 22°C and Durban 26°C.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  